Edition:
Quote: The most advanced innovation on this line was the dobbin, a wheeled truck that would hold about a yard of material. It was run on wooden rails extending from the cutting face to the adjacent gully or filling and added to as the work advanced, ... [114] ... On reaching the end of its run the dobbin was either spragged or tipped by means of a cradle.
